did.unittitle: Executive Papers of Governor Henry Carter Stuart, 1874-1918 (bulk 1914-1917)

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Virginia. Governor (1914-1918 : Stuart). Executive Papers of Governor Henry Carter Stuart, 1874-1918 (bulk 1914-1917). Accession 28722, State government records, Library of Virginia, Richmond, Va.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Transferred from the Governor's Office on 06/30/1975.

bioghist.head: Biographical Information
bioghist.p: Henry Carter Stuart, of Russell County, served as Governor from 1 February 1914 to 1 February 1918.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Executive Papers of Henry Carter Stuart are housed in seventy-two archival boxes and are arranged in alphabetical order by subject.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged into the following series:

list.item: Series I: Executive Papers of Governor Henry Carter Stuart, 1874-1918 (bulk 1914-1917)

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Material
separatedmaterial.p: Oversized items have been separated to Boxes 70-72.
